Many times it is useful to declare a class once and reuse it throughout a piece of code (e.g. plugins).

```
var CUSTOM_CLASS = '.class-name',
    $el = $(CUSTOM_CLASS);

...

if ($someEl.hasClass(CUSTOM_CLASS)) {
    $someEl.removeClass(CUSTOM_CLASS);
}

...

$someOtherEl.find(CUSTOM_CLASS);

// etc
```

However, this is not possible currently since `.addClass`, `.removeClass`, `.toggleClass`, and `.hasClass` do not accept class names which include the dot, while `$()` and most tree traversing methods either accept or require it.

I think it would be beneficial to allow these other methods to accept class names which include the dot.

