Due to JScript's [named function expression bug](http://kangax.github.com/nfe/#jscript-bugs), the click handler used in the `jQuery.support.noCloneEvent` test isn't actually removed in IE.

``` javascript
div.attachEvent("onclick", function click() {
  console.log(click === arguments.callee); // false
});
```

This leads to a memory leak in IE6 and IE7, but not IE8+ (I presume because of GC improvements).

My change uses a variable to reference this function instead, attaching and detaching the event handler is done in the same scope, and detaching is guaranteed even when events aren't cloned.

